headline: ACN Q4 Deep Dive: AI Momentum and Strategic Partnerships Drive Mixed Margin Story
summary: Global professional services company Accenture (NYSE:ACN) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 6% year on year to $18.74 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $17.68 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.94 per share was 5.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
